---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Tags from '../components/Tags.astro';
import Missions from '../components/Missions.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
      <div class="mast-container">
        <h1> 🚀</h1>
        <h1 class="main-heading">astrodeck.dev</h1>
      </div>
      <blockquote>
🧑‍🚀 Hello, Astronaut!
      </blockquote>

Welcome aboard astrodeck.dev — your personal mission control for all things front-end and beyond.
        <br />

This blog explores the intersection of UI design, UI development, and modern software engineering principles. Whether it's crafting sleek interfaces in React, diving into component-driven workflows, or refining elegant layouts, astrodeck.dev is where ideas lift off.

        <br />
Along the way, I’ll also share the projects I’m building, experiments I'm tinkering with, and the lessons learned navigating the ever-expanding universe of web development.
        <br />
If you’re passionate about clean design, thoughtful code, and tech that feels as good as it looks — you’re in the right orbit.
			</p>
      <Tags />
      <Missions />
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
